pageContext.claim: “[Gas prices are] low. And that doesn't happen by luck. I work hard on that. That's like a tax cut for people.”
pageContext.analysis: The president has little power to move prices at the gas pump in any direction because they depend on market forces beyond his control. A variety of market factors has contributed to the falling price of gasoline. Trump has previously suggested prices fell because of phone calls to foreign leaders in oil-rich countries, but that's a fallacy.
